<p>
  What worries me about these platforms is that they're products. You don't
  actually own your data like Wolfram does. One day these companies might go
  away and so will you data - and your opportunity for self-tracking. I think
  the only 'safe' way to do this kind of digital self-tracking is to learn how
  to code and do it yourself. E.g. you should be exporting your tweets, emails and 
  facebook data on a regular basis - and saving them to a disk that you
  own, not a disk that you rent.
</p>

